answers.body_markdown:
Try using property binding


```
&lt;div formArrayName=&quot;sample&quot; *ngFor=&quot;let a of sampledata; let i = index&quot;&gt;
  &lt;div [formGroupName]=&quot;i&quot;&gt;
    &lt;input type=&quot;text&quot; formControlName=&quot;i&quot; name=&quot;i&quot; [value]=&quot;i&quot; 
  /&gt;
  &lt;input
      formControlName=&quot;dx&quot;
      type=&quot;text&quot;
      class=&quot;form-control&quot;
    /&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
```

There are some points you have missed in your code, 

Because you are dealing with the `dynamic input tags`, you need to give the `unique name` to `formControlName` and that can be done with below code.

**P.S :** For value you don&#39;t need to add `{{}}`.

     &lt;div formArrayName=&quot;sample&quot; *ngFor=&quot;let a of sampledata; let i = index&quot;&gt;
          &lt;div [formGroupName]=&quot;index_{{i}}&quot;&gt;
            &lt;input type=&quot;text&quot; formControlName=&quot;index_{{i}}&quot; name=&quot;index_{{i}}&quot; value=&quot;i&quot;/&gt;
            &lt;input formControlName=&quot;dx_{{i}}&quot;  type=&quot;text&quot;  class=&quot;form-control&quot;  /&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;

Hope this helps.. :)

`*ngFor` should be placed after defining the formArray Name. You should change your html like below,

    &lt;div formArrayName=&quot;samples&quot;&gt;
    	&lt;div *ngFor=&quot;let a of getControls(sampledata, &#39;sample&#39;); let i = index&quot;
               [formGroupName]=&quot;i&quot;&gt;
    	&lt;input type=&quot;text&quot; formControlName=&quot;index&quot; name=&quot;index&quot; value=&quot;{{ i }}&quot;/&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

This should bind the value of i to your formControlName index.

Hope it helps. Cheers

Here is the working sample from stackblitz

https://stackblitz.com/edit/angular-cbqtmj

